**** INSTALLATION OF XFER DUMP INDEX UTILITY ****

1)  ASSEMBLE/LINK 'XFERVOL' INTO A LOADLIB
2)  ASSEMBLE/LINK 'XFERUTIL' WITH THE 'XFERVOL' LOADLIB AVAILABLE
      AS A 'SYSLIB' ON THE LINK STEP
3)  PLACE 'XFERUTIL' IN A 'LINKLIST' DATASET
4)  ASSEMBLE/LINK 'XFERWTO' AND PLACE IN LINKLIST DATASET
5)  ASSEMBLE/LINK 'XFERCPU' AND PLACE IN LINKLIST DATASET
6)  PLACE 'XFER1' AND 'XFER2' CLISTS IN YOUR SYSTEM CLIST LIBRARY
7)  PLACE 'XIX' 'JULDATE', 'BXFER',' AND 'EXFER', CLISTS IN YOUR
      SYSTEM CLIST LIBRARY
8)  ALLOCATE A PARTITIONED DATASET WITH THE FOLLOWING:
      RECFM(FB) LRECL(80) BLKSIZE(XXXXXX) DSORG(PO) DIR(XX)
9)  EDIT 'MAKEDAY' CLIST FOR CORRECT DATASET NAME AS ALLOCATED ABOVE
10) RUN 'MAKEDAY' TO INITIALIZE THE PDS FOR 'XFERDUMP'
11) TAILOR THE ' XFERJOB' JOBSTREAM FOR YOUR INSTALLTAION.
      ADD THE APPROPRIATE QUANTITY OF STEPS FOR THE CORRESPONDING
      QUANTITY OF DUMP DATASETS ON THE SYSTEM(S).
12) PLACE THE EDITED 'XFERJOB' IN A JOBRDR DEFINED LIBRARY
13) SET AMDPRDMP OPTIONS IN PARMLIB FOR THE 'XFERJOB'
14) MAKE SURE THE STEP THAT INVOKES THE TSO 'TMP' HAS THE CORRECT
    CLIST LIBRARIES ALLOCATED
